                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.113/53: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="from"
                        >Grew</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-06T14:00:00+09:00"
                            >March 6, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 6—2:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. The British Ambassador tells me that he believes there is a movement in his
                    own country to force the British Government to restrict the arms embargo to
                    apply to Japan exclusively, and that he has emphatically warned his Government
                    of the danger of such a step which would very likely cause Japan to blockade
                    Chinese ports resulting in the grave risk of a general war. I share his views in
                    this respect. Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
